						<summary>

						<p>On the south wall of the central shrine in the Agastyēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Vikramapāṇḍya.</p>						

						<p>The date is lost in the damaged portion.</p>						

						<p>This seems to record the sale of land to the <hi rend="italic">maṭha</hi> belonging to the Tiruchcheṟṟimuṟṟattu-santānam made free of taxes for 60 <hi rend="italic">paṇams</hi> by the <hi rend="italic">Ūravar.</hi> Other details are lost. </p>						

						</summary>
